weird mood i'm in a really weird mood it's not a good one either i'm just wishing i had friends well i have friends but only at school pretty much once school is out i don't have any kind of a social life this summer has been really hard for me i've had waaay to much time to think i really want to dance basically more than anything in life i want to give people chills but i'm too scared to go take lessons sort of that doesn't really explain it i live in the middle of nowhere can't really afford lessons i'm bored i'm tired of being bored all the time i'm tired of sitting and waiting for tomorrow and then doing it again i'm scared of everything i don't know i can't explain it i just want to dance and be good at it you have no idea sorry i know this wasn't a question please don't report me i just wanted to tell someone how i'm feeling gah that sounds so cliche and lame anyway yeah record shows with dancing in them get dvds or tapes do the napoleon dynamite thing and set up a room for starters get up early or whatever you have to do to have privacy to get you past the bashful stages it doesn't take long later expand to somewhere outside where no one bothers you and you become the best dancer on earth and by the end of summer you'll be freaking some people out later on remember hydrate often take some salt and don't forget to eat or you'll die once you begin keep at it there are worst things you could do with your summer now go make us proud Avenue Q The Ashlee Simpson Show Theory of conduct Wonderland (McFly album) Cliff Richard Time Out of Mind Little Britain "Weird Al" Yankovic Humphrey Bogart Napoleon Dynamite God Emperor of Dune Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Singlish She Loves You Milton H. Erickson The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind The Cure Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME The Emancipation of Mimi Piccolo Junior Saga Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Tina Turner Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The Grim Adventures of Billy a